entries.definition:
w–l–d newly born baby, boy, child, offspring; mother, father,
parents; to give birth, to assist in bringing forth a baby, midwife;
to multiply in number; place or time of birth; playmates. Of this
root, 11 forms occur 102 times in the Qur’an: وَلَد walada six
times; وُلِد wulida three times; وَلَد walad 33 times; أَوْلَاد ʾawlād 23
times; وَالِد wālid three times; وَالِدَان wālidān 20 times;
وَالِدَة wālidatun three times; وَالِدَات wālidāt once; وَلِيد walīd once;
وِلْدَان wildān six times and مَوْلُود mawlūd three times.

1046

